                <h2 class="intro">Introduction</h2>

                <p>
                    I am Pheello Mokoena, a software engineer who lives in the town of Qalabotjha, in the province of Free State, in South Africa. I can describe myself as a person who has a strong
                    zeal for growing in knowledge, not only tech related knowledge but business knowledge and any other knowledge that can make me a better version of myself everyday. The majority of my time everyday is allocated to studying or working on software solutions, that aim at achieving at least two things for my potential clients:
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Efficiency in business operations:</strong> Before I commit to working on a project, I ask myself if the solution I want to develop or that the client wants, has the potential to make them more efficient in the way they go about doing their daily operations, for example, will the solution reduce the time spent doing a specific task or will it reduce the cost of doing that task, thereby making them more efficient?</li>
                        <li><strong>Increasing revenue:</strong> Another factor I consider is whether the solution has the potential to improve the client's revenue generation, for example, if the solution can reduce costs, can the client see the opportunity to increase the profit margins, or if the solution makes them more efficient in their business operations, can they therefore increase their sales volume thereby increasing their revenue?</li>
                    </ul>
                </p>
