            <div class="exp-cnt">

                <h2 class="experience">Experience</h2>

                <p>
                    Of all the software solutions I have worked on, there are two that are customer oriented that I will talk about as part of my experience developing software solutions. One was a group project I contributed to in 2025 for our final year Informatics project at the University of Johannesburg.
                </p>

                <p>
                    According to our client which was a secondary school, they wanted to have a way of enabling parents to monitor their children's academic progress and attendance behavior. The solution had to provide a method to allow learners to take an attendance code and submit it using a mobile app, this way the solution would then summarise the attendance records of each learner and produce reports that are easier for the users (parents & learners) to understand, informing the parent on their child's attendance behavior.
                </p>

                <p>
                    Concerning monitoring academic performance, the teachers had to upload their learners' marks after marking, then again the solution would process the marks and produce summaries showing how well or bad the learners are performing academically. The parents and learners were to make use of a mobile app while teachers were to use a web application.
                </p>

                <p>
                    The mobile application was developed using the following technologies: <strong>Dart programming language</strong>, <strong>Flutter framework</strong>, and <strong>fl_chart</strong> for graphically representing summaries. The web application was developed using the following technologies: <strong>ASP.NET Core MVC</strong> for the web app, <strong>ASPNET Core Web API</strong> for the Web API, and <strong>Microsoft SQL Server</strong> for storing learners' marks and attendance records.
                </p>

                <p>
                    Another solution I have worked on alone, is an inventory management web application. With this solution, a stock manager or business owner is able to monitor their stock movements, and if inventory levels reach a certain treshold the solution will inform the stock manager via email informing him that a reorder is required, in addition the solution generates stock reports which inform stock managers of items that need to be reordered.
                </p>

                <p>
                    Another functionality provided by this solution is revenue and purchases report generation. Revenue reports show how the business has been performing monthly by comparing monthly revenues for the past months and which products and categories of products are performing well or not well. Purchases reports show how the business has been spending cash on buying inventory and compares these monthly costs as well as which products and categories did the business spend more or less on.
                </p>
